text: Walsaqucha (Quechua walsa raft, qucha lake, "raft lake", Hispanicized spelling Balsacocha) is a lake in Peru located in the Junín Region, Huancayo Province, Chongos Alto District. It is situated between Yuraqqucha in the north and Aqchiqucha in the south.
